<title>USA: Staar to start contact lens trials.</title>
<headline>Staar to start contact lens trials.</headline>
<dateline>MONROVIA, Calif. 1997-02-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>STAAR Surgical Co said the U.S. Food and Drug Administration granted it an Investigational Device Exemption to begin human clinical trials of its implantable contact lens.</p>
<p>The lens, designed to correct mild to severe nearsightedness and farsightedness, is permanently implanted into the eye using the same process the company has used in cataract surgery procedures.</p>
